ideasfamous people born in mississippishow all groupsfamous people born on april famous people born in united statesfamous people born in hickoryfamous people born in famous people in televisionfamous university of illinois alumnifamous business leadersfamous people named johnsonfamous people in basketballfamous freeport high school alumnifamous ariansafricanamerican firsts athletesfamous princeton university alumniafrican americanentrepreneurfamous people in businessafricanamerican firsts entrepreneursafricanamerican firsts film  tvfamous people named robertsynopsisrobert l johnson was born on april   in hickory mississippi johnson founded black entertainment television bet in  with his wife sheila he became the first africanamerican billionaire after selling the network to viacom in  johnson has since started a new business the rlj companies and has invested in an nba team a film company and political causes and campaignsearly liferobert l johnson was born in hickory mississippi on april   he spent the majority of his childhood in freeport illinois johnson graduated from freeport high school in  and studied history at the university of illinois he then earned a master’s degree in international affairs from princeton universitycareerin  johnson and his wife sheila founded black entertainment television the first cable network targeting the africanamerican market it was launched in january  initially broadcasting for two hours a week in  bet became the first african americanowned company to be listed on the new york stock exchange the network has continued to grow since that time reaching tens of millions of homes and expanding to include other traditional and digital channels in  viacom announced plans to purchase bet the sale was finalized the following year and johnson’s majority stake earned him more than  billion making him the richest african american in the united states at that time as well as the first africanamerican billionaire johnson continued to be the company’s chairman and ceo for several years before leaving bet to lead the rlj companies johnson developed the rlj companies following the sale of bet to viacom rlj is a holding company and asset management firm handling a portfolio of companies in the financial services real estate hospitality professional sports film production automotive and gaming industries johnson has referred to rlj as his “second act” johnson has invested in several notable companies and organizations beyond the reach of rlj he was the first africanamerican principal owner of a north american majorleague sports franchise the charlotte bobcats in  johnson founded our stories films with partner harvey weinstein the company focuses on familyfriendly movies intended for africanamerican audiences in  our stories released the romanticcomedy feature jumping the broom in addition to his business ventures johnson has involved himself in politics in  johnson organized a tour of africanamerican business leaders to liberia this trip led to the creation of the liberia enterprise development fund johnson publicly called for africanamerican support of liberia on the model of jewish support for israel johnson received criticism for his rebuke of barack obama during the  democratic primary election in favor of hillary clintonpersonal lifejohnson was married to sheila johnson from  to  the couple who cofounded bet divorced a year after selling the network to viacom they have two children sheila johnson received one of the largest documented settlements in united states history and subsequently married the judge who presided over the divorce proceedingsfact checkwe strive for accuracy and fairness if you see something that doesnt look right contact uscitation informationarticle titlerobert l johnson biographycomauthorbiographycom editorswebsite namethe biographycom websiteurlhttpswwwbiographycompeoplerobertljohnsonaccess datepublisherae television networkslast updatedapril  original published datenasharesbio